India’s Sensex Extends Losses; Declines 1.5 Percent to 17,671.8

-- B y   R a j h k u m a r   K   S h a a w
-- 
2011-08-04T09:41:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-04/india-s-sensex-extends-losses-declines-1-5-percent-to-17-671-8.html
Indian stocks extended declines. The
Bombay Stock Exchange Sensitive Index lost 1.5 percent to
17,671.81 at 3:05 p.m. in Mumbai. Mahindra & Mahindra Ltd.,
 India ’s largest maker of sport-utility vehicles and tractors,
sank 4.4 percent. ITC Ltd., the biggest cigarette company,
retreated 3.3 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
